headlines.description: — Jerami Grant and Frank Jackson scored 18 points apiece to lift the Detroit Pistons to a 100-86 victory over the Atlanta Hawks on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Dunn returns, but Hawks fall 100-86 to Pistons

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Orlando Magic

headlines.description: — Dennis Schroder scored 13 of 21 points in the fourth quarter, Anthony Davis added 18 points and eight rebounds and the Los Angeles Lakers rallied in the fourth quarter to beat the Orlando Magic 114-103 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Schroder, Davis lead Lakers' late rally past Magic

headlines.description: — Joel Embiid scored 21 points, Ben Simmons had 12 in his return to the lineup and the Philadelphia 76ers beat Oklahoma City 121-90 on Monday night, sending the Thunder to their franchise record-tying 14th straight loss.
headlines.shortLinkText: 76ers hand Thunder franchise worst-tying 14th straight loss

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Washington Wizards

headlines.description: — DeMar DeRozan had 37 points and 10 assists, and the San Antonio Spurs outlasted the Wizards 146-143 in overtime on Monday night, ending Washington's season-best eight-game winning streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Spurs outlast Wizards in OT, end Washington's streak at 8

events.name: Phoenix Suns at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Devin Booker scored 33 points and the Phoenix Suns capped a grueling road trip with a 118-110 victory Monday night that snapped the New York Knicks' nine-game winning streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Suns snap Knicks' nine-game win streak with 118-110 victory

headlines.description: — Pascal Siakam scored 25 points, rookie Malachi Flynn added 18 and the Toronto Raptors pulled away in the second half for a 112-96 win over the depleted Cleveland Cavaliers on Monday night.
— Nikola Vucevic scored 24 points, Daniel Theis added 23 and the Chicago Bulls moved closer to the last play-in spot in the Eastern Conference by beating the Miami Heat 110-102 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bulls hold off Heat late, win 110-102 in Miami

headlines.description: — D’Angelo Russell had a season-high seven 3-pointers and scored 27 points, and Karl-Anthony Towns had 21 points and 11 rebounds as the Minnesota Timberwolves rallied to beat the Utah Jazz 105-104 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Timberwolves beat Jazz for 3rd time this season, 105-104

events.name: LA Clippers at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Zion Williamson scored 23 points on an array of power moves, spinning dribbles and even a 3-pointer, and the New Orleans Pelicans beat the Los Angeles Clippers 120-103 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Williamson scores 23, leads Pelicans past Clippers, 120-103

headlines.description: — Michael Porter Jr. erupted for 31 points courtesy of a torrid shooting night, Paul Millsap added nine of his 12 points in the fourth quarter and the short-handed Denver Nuggets beat the Memphis Grizzlies 120-96 on Monday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Porter scores 31 points, Nuggets knock off Grizzlies 120-96

headlines.description: — Tyrese Haliburton had 14 points and 10 assists in his second straight start in place of leading scorer De’Aaron Fox, and the Sacramento Kings beat the Dallas Mavericks113-106 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Fox-less Kings jump on Mavs early, win 113-106
